### Build-a-Bank · Step 12 · Demand Account — accounts, transfers & the double-entry ledger
### 1) Start Postgres:  docker compose -f services/demand-account/compose.yaml up -d
###    (maps host 5433 → container 5432 to avoid the local Postgres on 5432 — see CAPABILITIES.md)
### 2) Start the service:
###    SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5433/demand_account ./mvnw -pl services/demand-account spring-boot:run
###    (port 8082)

@host = http://localhost:8082

### Open account A with $200 → 201 Created
POST {{host}}/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{"accountNumber":"ACC-A","currency":"USD","openingBalance":200.00}

### Open account B with $0 → 201 Created
POST {{host}}/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{"accountNumber":"ACC-B","currency":"USD","openingBalance":0.00}

### Transfer $50 A → B → 200 OK + the transactionId of the two ledger legs
POST {{host}}/api/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{"from":"ACC-A","to":"ACC-B","amount":50.00,"description":"rent"}

### Check A's balance → 200 (now 150.00)
GET {{host}}/api/accounts/ACC-A

### Check B's balance → 200 (now 50.00)
GET {{host}}/api/accounts/ACC-B

### Try to overdraw A (only 150 left) → 422 Unprocessable Entity {"error":"insufficient_funds"}
POST {{host}}/api/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{"from":"ACC-A","to":"ACC-B","amount":9999.00,"description":"too much"}

### Unknown account → 400 Bad Request
POST {{host}}/api/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{"from":"ACC-A","to":"NOPE","amount":1.00}

### See applied Flyway migrations
GET {{host}}/actuator/flyway
